<task id="R3-032" project="spaarke-platform-foundations-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Define + implement `sprk_organization` user-mapping mechanism</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed-date>2026-06-21</completed-date>
    <completion-notes>
      Mechanism chosen: Option (b) — configurable Lookup field on sprk_organization
      pointing to systemuser. Operators set
      Membership:OrganizationLookup:UserLookupField to the field's logical name
      (e.g., sprk_owneruser). When unset, the resolver returns an empty list and
      logs Info once per process (fail-soft default).

      Files created:
        - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Membership/IOrganizationMembershipResolver.cs
        - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Membership/OrganizationMembershipResolver.cs
        - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Membership/Models/PersonIdentity.cs (placeholder; replaced by task 031 with full shape)
        - tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Membership/OrganizationMembershipResolverTests.cs
        - projects/spaarke-platform-foundations-r3/notes/sprk-organization-mapping-decision.md
        - projects/spaarke-platform-foundations-r3/notes/bff-publish-size-task032.md

      Files modified:
        - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Membership/MembershipOptions.cs
          (added OrganizationLookupOptions nested record + OrganizationLookup property)
        - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/MembershipModule.cs
          (registered OrganizationMembershipResolver as singleton behind both
          IOrganizationMembershipResolver canonical contract AND task 031's
          IIdentityOrganizationResolver seam)

      Coordination with task 031: parallel agent created
      IIdentityOrganizationResolver with a different signature
      (ResolveOrganizationsAsync(systemUserId, contactId, ct)) and the full
      PersonIdentity record shape. Resolved by having the concrete
      OrganizationMembershipResolver implement BOTH interfaces. The
      IIdentityOrganizationResolver method delegates to the canonical
      task-032 method and ignores the contactId parameter (Option b keys
      off systemuser only).

      Operator follow-up needed: yes — operators wanting non-empty mappings
      must configure UserLookupField to point at a Lookup column on
      sprk_organization targeting systemuser. Decision note documents the
      runbook steps. Environments that do nothing get fail-soft empty
      results.

      Tests: 7 passed (no-mapping, empty-userid, zero-rows, three-rows
      with FetchXml inspection, exception fail-soft, cap honouring,
      cancellation propagation)
      Build: pass (0 errors, 0 warnings on BFF csproj)
      Publish size: 46.16 MB (+0.02 MB vs 46.14 MB baseline)
      CVE: no new HIGH
    </completion-notes>
    <phase>P4</phase>
    <parallel-group>G (with 030, 031)</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
